Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
verifyIO2BumpConnectivity(25.10)              verifyIO2BumpConnectivity(25.10)

Name
       verifyIO2BumpConnectivity - Verifies multiBump multiPad connectivity

Syntax
       verifyIO2BumpConnectivity

       [-help]

       [-error <integer>]

       [-report <string>]

        [-subclass <string>]

       [-warning <integer>]

       [-bump_connect_target | -class_bump ]

       [-bumps <string> | -class_bump ]

       [-bumps <string> | -nets <string>]

       Verifies multiBump multiPad connectivity. The flip chip flow in Innovus
       supports  multiple  pads  to  multiple bumps connections. Use the veri-
       fyIO2BumpConnectivity command, instead of verifyConnectivity to  verify
       such connections.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each verifyIO2BumpConnectivity parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man verifyIO2BumpConnectivity

       -bump_connect_target
              Checks  only  whether  or not the routing matches the connection
              specified by bump_connect_target properties (  io:pin:port)  re-
              gardless of the class of the port.

       -bumps <string>
              Specifies the name of the bumps that are to be checked.

       -class_bump
              Checks only whether or not the ports of CLASS BUMP are routed to
              the bumps regardless of the  bump_connect_target properties.

       -error <integer>
              Specifies the maximum number of errors to report.

       -nets <string>
              Specifies the names of the nets that are to be checked.

       -report <string>
              Specifies the name of the report file in which verifyIO2BumpCon-
              nectivity violation data is recorded.

              Default: designname.io2bump.rpt

       -subclass <string>
              Specifies the name of the subclasses of which the wires and vias
              are to be checked.

       -warning <integer>
              Specifies the maximum number of warnings to report.

Related Information
       The Identifying and Viewing Violations chapter of User Guide.

